---
// Figma file u4NLOVKuXUTKULhSn0sAJQ, node 1:23922 ("Desktop", Portfolio frame).
// Hero region nodes (canvas y, from get_metadata on content group 1:23924):
//   eyebrow 1:25510 "PORTFOLIO" (y311.55, real text, reported Faculty Glyphic but a
//     5x zoomed get_screenshot shows plain sans strokes, no serifs on P/O/R/T/F/L —
//     the same "wrapping-group misreports Faculty" correction used site-wide;
//     corrected to --font-sans here), underline 1:25509 (y391.67, w188.25 — BYTE-
//     IDENTICAL width to About/Initiatives' own hairline underlines, same shared
//     construction, reused numbers), chevron 1:25511 (down arrow, path data
//     BYTE-IDENTICAL to src/assets/home/scroll-arrow.svg — reused directly, no new
//     asset).
//   H1 1:25514 "The builders" (y419.12) / 1:25515 "we're backing." (y506.69, curly
//     apostrophe verified in the node's own characters string) — get_design_context
//     shows the accent span covers only the word "backing" (not the trailing
//     period), fill #ff7400 (--color-orange-bright, the same accent token About/
//     Team already use for H1/eyebrow accents). Base fill #1e1e3e ~= --color-ink-alt
//     (#1e1e3c), within this file's usual Illustrator-import noise.
//   Lede 1:25516 (y633.61, outlined/no real text) "Our individual partners have
//     been backing energy innovations for years. Now, we are all coming together
//     to do it." — font-size/line-height reuse the site's established 1.9375rem/
//     1.31 constant (independently re-derived via Sora-glyph-metrics on About's and
//     Initiatives' own ledes and confirmed to always converge on the same value
//     for this weight/face; this page's own 3-line frame height is consistent with
//     that constant within the usual outlined-bbox ink-only-bounds slack).
//   Info bar 1:25367 (y809.11, bordered pill, border 1:25368 stroke #1e1e3c i.e.
//     --color-ink-alt): badge 1:25504 (orange circle w/ navy ring, flattened
//     raster-in-context but trivially a CSS circle — no asset needed, verified via
//     get_design_context) overlaps the pill's own left rounded end by 49.26px
//     (badge x483 vs pill-border x532.26, both sharing the same right edge
//     1475.72); "i" glyph 1:25507 (real text, y823.71, centered in the badge);
//     paragraph 1:25369 (y829.52, outlined) "Ventures backed across the energy
//     majors. A selection of companies incubated through the energy majors'
//     programmes. MC²+ Cohort 1 onboards from August 2026." — copy verified via
//     get_design_context screenshot.
//   Decor: hero-curves.svg (Task 1 export, combined from nodes 1:25612 + 1:25614,
//     converted from each node's own local path coords into one shared 1920-wide
//     canvas frame) + spark-a.svg (node 1:25616) / spark-b.svg (node 1:25615).
import HeroCurves from "../../assets/portfolio/hero-curves.svg";
import SparkA from "../../assets/portfolio/spark-a.svg";
import SparkB from "../../assets/portfolio/spark-b.svg";
import ScrollArrow from "../../assets/home/scroll-arrow.svg";
import RevealStar from "../../assets/shared/reveal-star.svg";
---

<section class="hero">
  <div class="orbit" aria-hidden="true">
    <HeroCurves class="curves" />
    <SparkA class="spark spark-a" />
    <SparkB class="spark spark-b" />
  </div>

  <div class="hero-inner reveal">
    <p class="eyebrow">PORTFOLIO</p>
    <div class="underline" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <h1>
      <span class="line reveal-line">
        <span class="reveal-line-box">
          <span class="reveal-line-text">The builders</span>
          <RevealStar class="reveal-star" aria-hidden="true" />
        </span>
      </span>
      <span class="line reveal-line">
        <span class="reveal-line-box">
          <span class="reveal-line-text">we&rsquo;re <span class="accent">backing</span>.</span>
          <RevealStar class="reveal-star" aria-hidden="true" />
        </span>
      </span>
    </h1>

    <p class="lede reveal-rise reveal-rise--after-2-lines">
      Our individual partners have been backing energy innovations for
      years. Now, we are all coming together to do it.
    </p>

    <div class="info-bar">
      <div class="info-badge" aria-hidden="true">i</div>
      <p class="info-text">
        Ventures backed across the energy majors. A selection of companies
        incubated through the energy majors&rsquo; programmes. MC&sup2;+
        Cohort 1 onboards from August 2026.
      </p>
    </div>

    <ScrollArrow class="scroll" aria-hidden="true" />
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .hero {
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--color-cream);
    /* padding-top derived from the design's own header height (node 1:25617,
       y0.14-110.79, i.e. 110.65px) vs the live shared header's own rendered
       height (90.1875px, getBoundingClientRect — the same constant Home/
       Initiatives' Hero.astro already cite for this identical component):
       eyebrow (1:25510, canvas y311.55) sits 311.55-110.65 = 200.9px below
       the design's own header bottom, so the live page needs that same
       200.9px of clearance after the live header ends (algebraic value
       12.556rem). A headless-Chrome render at 1920 with that value landed
       the eyebrow ink 6px low (anti-aliased cap-height detection offset,
       not a real spacing error); tightened by that same 6px (0.375rem) to
       12.18rem, verified pixel-exact (row 291 = target 291) at 1920. */
    padding-top: 12.18rem;
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  }
  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    .hero {
      /* CORRECTED (fix round 1): a fresh get_screenshot of node 1:23922 shows
         both curves emerging exactly at the shared header's own bottom edge —
         i.e. the design's curve canvas (1:25612/1:25614, starting at canvas
         y34.71) sits PARTLY BEHIND the header (header height 110.65px, node
         1:25617), not "already clear of it" as this comment previously and
         wrongly claimed. Same convention as Initiatives' Hero: min-height is
         sized off the curve box's height MINUS the header (1086 - 110.65 =
         975.35px = 60.96rem at the 1920 reference, 975.35/1920 = 50.80vw). */
      min-height: clamp(40rem, 50.8vw, 60.96rem);
    }
  }

  /* Curves + sparks: decorative, absolutely positioned behind copy. Sparks are
     separate sibling nodes (1:25616/1:25615, Task 1 export), positioned as
     percentages of the curves SVG's own 1920x1086 box so they stay locked to
     the curve intersections at any viewport width (same technique as Home's/
     Initiatives' own Hero.astro).
     top offset (fix round 1): shifts the curve canvas UP by the shared
     header's own live rendered height (90.1875px = 5.6367rem, the same
     constant Home/Initiatives already cite for this identical component) so
     canvas y0 re-aligns with true page y0 — matching the design, where the
     header sits IN FRONT of (not after) the curve canvas's own origin. Without
     this, the curves rendered a full header-height too low AND with their
     top ~110px never clipped by the header, showing extra never-meant-to-be-
     visible geometry (the "complete circle floating clear of the navbar"
     bug) instead of the design's own curves-emerge-from-under-the-header look. */
  .orbit {
    position: absolute;
    top: -5.6367rem;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    z-index: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .curves {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }
  .spark {
    position: absolute;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
  }
  .spark-a {
    /* node 1:25616: center (565.0, 311.12) / (1920, 1086) box */
    left: 29.43%;
    top: 28.65%;
    width: 5.0rem; /* 80.13px natural size, applied at ~83% for legibility parity with other pages' sparks */
    height: 4.19rem;
  }
  .spark-b {
    /* node 1:25615: center (1860.7, 324.68) / (1920, 1086) box */
    left: 96.91%;
    top: 29.9%;
    width: 3.32rem; /* 53.13px natural size */
    height: 2.69rem;
  }

  .hero-inner {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    /* Was 51rem (sized only for H1/lede's own 766.26px column). The info-bar
       (node 1:25367) is measurably WIDER — 992.72px — and since .info-badge is
       position:absolute (removed from flex flow) plus .info-bar's own 49.26px
       left margin reserving room for the badge overhang, a 51rem wrapper only
       left 726.75px available (measured live), squeezing the info-bar's text
       to 3 lines instead of Figma's 2 and making the correctly-sized badge
       read as oversized next to a visibly cramped pill. 67.65rem clears
       992.72 + 49.26(margin) + 40(padding) = 1081.98px with a small buffer;
       H1's lines are pre-broken per-line spans and .lede has its own
       independent max-width+auto margins, so neither is affected by widening
       this shared wrapper. */
    max-width: 67.65rem;
    margin-inline: auto;
    padding-inline: 1.25rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-sans); /* corrected from Figma's reported Faculty Glyphic — see frontmatter comment */
    font-size: var(--text-hero-eyebrow); /* 27.07px, node 1:25510 — identical to SectionHeading's own eyebrow size — normalized to home hero scale per user directive 2026-07-06 */
    letter-spacing: 0.25em; /* 6.7675px / 27.07px, node 1:25510 */
    color: var(--color-gray); /* #949494 sampled, within noise of --color-gray #959595 */
  }
  .underline {
    width: 11.77rem; /* 188.25px, node 1:25509 — byte-identical to About/Initiatives' own hairline underline */
    height: 1px;
    margin: 2.82rem auto 1.72rem; /* 45.12px eyebrow-bottom→underline; 27.45px underline→H1-top, both this page's own measurements */
    background: #000; /* one-off literal, node 1:25509's own sampled stroke (black, not a token) */
  }

  h1 {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-hero-h1); /* 80px, nodes 1:25514/1:25515 — normalized to home hero scale per user directive 2026-07-06 */
    line-height: var(--text-hero-h1-lh); /* baseline delta 87.57px (506.69-419.12) / 80px = 1.095, this page's own measurement — normalized to home hero scale per user directive 2026-07-06 */
    color: var(--color-ink-alt); /* #1e1e3e sampled, within noise of --color-ink-alt #1e1e3c */
  }
  h1 .line {
    display: block;
  }
  h1 .accent {
    color: var(--color-orange-bright); /* #ff7400 exact match, node 1:25515's own "backing" span fill */
  }

  .lede {
    max-width: 47.89rem; /* 766.26px, node 1:25516's own bounding width, matches H1's own column */
    margin: 1.4325rem auto 4.06rem; /* 22.92px H1-bottom→lede-top; 64.95px lede-bottom→info-bar-top, both this page's own measurements */
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-hero-lede); /* 31px — reused site-wide lede constant, see frontmatter comment — normalized to home hero scale per user directive 2026-07-06 */
    line-height: var(--text-hero-lede-lh); /* derived — see frontmatter comment — normalized to home hero scale per user directive 2026-07-06 */
    color: var(--color-ink-alt);
  }

  .info-bar {
    position: relative;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    width: 62.045rem; /* 992.72px, node 1:25367 — was max-width only, which let the bar shrink-to-fit its content (text+padding, ~944px) below Figma's fixed box size since inline-flex never grows past what content needs; explicit width forces the exact figma size regardless */
    max-width: 100%;
    margin-inline: 3.079rem 0; /* clears space for the badge's own left overhang (49.26px, see below) so the whole component still centers under the copy column */
    border: 0.125rem solid var(--color-ink-alt); /* 2px, node 1:25368's own sampled stroke color; house convention for bordered pills (PillButton.ghost) uses the same 2px weight */
    /* Asymmetric, not a uniform stadium shape: the pill's raw SVG path (node
       1:25368) shows a full semicircular cap on the right (radius 42.5, half
       the pill height) but a distinctly SMALLER, tighter curve on the left
       (~36.24px radius) — the pill's own left edge is shaped to nest around
       the badge circle, not a plain rounded end. border-radius:999px on both
       corners (a normal pill) left the true corner curve peeking out past the
       badge in a screenshot comparison; matching the tighter left radius
       tucks it fully behind the badge instead. */
    border-radius: 2.265rem 999px 999px 2.265rem;
    padding: 0 2.971rem 0 3.817rem; /* 47.53px right / 61.07px left, node 1:25369's own inset from the pill border (1:25368) */
    min-height: 5.28rem; /* 84.51px, node 1:25368 */
  }
  .info-badge {
    position: absolute;
    left: -3.079rem; /* -49.26px, node 1:25504's own left edge vs the pill border's left edge (1:25368) — the badge overlaps the pill's left rounded end */
    top: 50%;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    width: 5.344rem; /* 85.5px diameter, node 1:25504 */
    height: 5.344rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-orange);
    border: 0.125rem solid var(--color-ink-alt);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-family: var(--font-display); /* node 1:25507 reports Faculty Glyphic; genuinely serif on screenshot (matches the "i" glyph's own visible serif foot) */
    font-size: 2.747rem; /* 43.95px, node 1:25507 */
    color: var(--color-ink-alt); /* screenshot shows navy ink (matches the badge's own ring), not the wrapper-reported black */
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .info-text {
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 52.18rem; /* 834.86px, node 1:25369's own bounding width */
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    /* 20px matches node 1:25369's own cap-height exactly (re-verified via get_metadata
       glyph heights, ~13.76px caps / 0.7 ratio ≈ 19.7px), and the box is Figma-exact
       834.86px — but at 20px, this site's Sora rendering wraps to 3 lines instead of
       Figma's 2 (a real web-font-metric difference, not a wrong number: Figma's own
       glyphs fit 2 lines at this exact width). Tested 20/19/18.5/18px directly via
       Playwright line-count; 19px is the first size that reproduces the 2-line wrap. */
    font-size: 1.1875rem; /* 19px */
    line-height: 1.27;
    color: var(--color-ink-alt);
    text-align: left;
  }

  .scroll {
    display: block;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    margin: 3rem auto 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 1023.98px) {
    h1 {
      font-size: var(--text-hero-h1-fluid); /* was clamp(2.4rem, 7vw, 5rem) — normalized to home hero scale per user directive 2026-07-06 */
    }
    .lede {
      max-width: 90%;
    }
    .spark {
      display: none; /* sanctioned adaptation, same rationale as Initiatives Hero: sparks drift onto copy below the design's own desktop breakpoint */
    }
    .info-bar {
      /* Sanctioned adaptation (design is desktop-only): the wide fixed pill
         can't survive a narrow viewport, so it collapses to a stacked card,
         same treatment as Initiatives' own notice bar. */
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
      max-width: 90%;
      margin-inline: auto;
      border-radius: 1.5rem;
      padding: 1.75rem 1.5rem;
      gap: 1rem;
    }
    .info-badge {
      position: static;
      transform: none;
      width: 3.5rem;
      height: 3.5rem;
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 639.98px) {
    .info-bar {
      max-width: 100%;
    }
  }
</style>
